<p>&#8220;Financial capital, whatever it is, is not an input into any material production process.&#8221;</p>
<p>Thank you very much for that. Piketty has me thinking very hard about this again. Real + financial capital = total capital. But hey: financial &#8220;capital&#8221; is claims, at some remove(s), on real capital. ?? The Homogeneous Lump of Capital fallacy?</p>
<p>He addresses this only is one passing paragraph in the context of &#8220;public&#8221; capital on p. 124, far removed from his definition of capital on p. 46.</p>
<p>Would love to see SRW&#8217;s mind brought to bear on that &#8220;whatever it is&#8221; question&#8230;</p>
