		<li id="comment-37440">
						<div class="commentbyline"><a href='http://deleted' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Noni Mausa</a> writes:</div>
						
                        <div class="commenttext"><p>PS  of course, it follows that if money is a lever to direct the efforts of others, than a steeply unequal society will consist of a majority of people whose seed stock of personal energy is not even available to themselves.   Rather, it is directed via a system that values or devalues them and their personal preferences and holds their lives and their families as impersonal hostages.  </p>
<p>No wonder we see outbursts of aggression and self-harm in such a society, and no wonder those outbursts seem senseless.  Putting a finger on the exact clump of mud that&#8217;s pulling you down when you&#8217;re in a patch of quicksand isn&#8217;t possible, so flailing about is one sensible, though fruitless, response.</p>
<p>Noni</p>
